AGI - After India's massive attack against targets in Pakistan, it was another night of fencing along the control line that acts as a border in Kashmir. Indian and Pakistani soldiers exchanged gunshots» during, reported sources of both countries.
As announced by Pakistani military spokesman Ahmed Sharif Chaudhry, Islamabad forces shot along the control line after being allowed to "respond for self-defense" in "time, place and way of their choice". The Indian army reported shooting with "light weapons and artillery guns" in several sites > during the night, and that its soldiers "reportedly."
In New Delhi this morning the details of Operation Sindoor were illustrated, in a press conference of Foreign Minister Vikram Misri, Commander Wing Vyomika Singh and Colonel Sophiya Qureshi. Nine "terroristic sites" targeted in retaliation for the April 22 attack in Pahalgam in Kashmir. The military showed a video of the precision attacks on the fields where terrorists would train. Now India awaits the likely reaction of Pakistan. "We will see every drop of the blood of these martyrs," said Pakistan's prime minister Shehbaz Sharif yesterday.
&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
At least thirteen civilians were killed and 59 wounded by Pakistani forces in the Kashmir dispute, after yesterday's massive Indian attack on nine "terroristic goals" in Pakistan. The Indian Foreign Ministry reported it. The victims of the attacks, "in violation of ceasefire", were all in the city of Poonch. In the same town yesterday an Indian military was killed.
A person died in drone attacks that India has taken on targets in Pakistan. The Pakistani army reported it. Twelve drones launched, one of which " managed to engage a military target near Lahore", announced the military spokesman Ahmed Sharif Chaudhry. In the raids, a civilian died and four Pakistani soldiers were injured, said the spokesman.&nbsp;
